{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place milk, malt extract and yeast in mixing bowl then heat <b>2 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add treacle, butter and 200 g buttermilk then heat <b>2 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add remaining 200 g buttermilk, plain flour, wholemeal flour, salt, bicarbonate of soda and garlic then knead <b>2 min\/<b>. Meanwhile, line a baking tray with baking paper and dust with flour. The dough will be very sticky. Tip out onto a well-floured surface and knead by hand for 1-2 minutes, adding more flour if needed. Form into a ball and place on prepared baking tray. Leave to prove in a warm place for 40 minutes. Towards the end of this time, preheat oven to 185°C.","Cut a cross on top of the dough with an oiled knife or press the handle of a wooden spoon to make a deep impression. Bake for 20 minutes (185°C).","Brush with olive oil. Sprinkle over sliced red onion, then sprinkle over sunflower seeds and coarse sea salt. Bake for 20 minutes (185°C) until deep golden brown and the bread sounds hollow when tapped underneath.","Place on a wire rack to cool. Serve with smoked mackerel pâté or soup of your choice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["75 g milk","15 g barley malt extract","30 g fresh yeast, crumbled","15 g black treacle, melted","50 g unsalted butter, melted","400 g buttermilk, plus extra for dusting","250 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","250 g wholemeal flour","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","10 g bicarbonate of soda, chopped","40 g garlic cloves, chopped","30 g olive oil, finely sliced","1 red onion, finely sliced","20 g sunflower seeds, for sprinkling","coarse sea salt, for sprinkling"]}],"id":"r178681","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-31CULybuYSQ\/XZWrwOfB1iI\/AAAAAAAAfsU\/sLzFBUj3jUwYxxluhyrkiPCMZibI02BBgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_u6W2SypDwSixxZ5U.png","title":"Red Onion and Garlic Soda Bread","publishedAt":"2017-10-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"83 g","fat":"95 g","uom":"per 1 Total recipe","carbohydrates":